definition: Tanegashima, Japanese Island off Kyushu, the Japanese space launch site

son/child/seed/egg/small thing/1st earthly branch: 11 p.m.-1 a.m., midnight, 11th solar month (7th December to 5th January), year of the Rat/Viscount, fourth of five orders of nobility 五等爵位[wu3 deng3 jue2 wei4]/ancient Chinese compass point: 0° (north)

sentences.english: The rocket blasted off successfully from the Japanese space center on Tanegashima Island in the Pacific Ocean.
sentences.chinese: 火箭從太平洋上的種子島太空中心成功發射升空。

sentences.english: The rocket was launched from Japan's Yoshinobu Launch Complex at the Tanegashima Space Center.
sentences.chinese: 火箭是從位於種子島太空中心的吉信發射區發射。

sentences.english: SDF personnel will be based in the dormitory in the Tanegashima. U.
sentences.chinese: 自衛隊員將常駐，宿舍在種子島。
